c({"name": "rootfolder", "type": "page", "comment": "<p>The root folder is the folder where DoneJS is installed (the folder which has\nfuncunit, jquery, steal, documentjs, etc).  </p>\n\n<p>Typically, the root folder should be a public folder that serves static content.</p>\n\n<p>steal references files from the root folder.  Also, paths that begin with \"//\" also reference the root folder:</p>\n\n<pre><code>steal('//foo/bar') // -&gt; ROOTFOLDER/foo/bar\ncan.view('//views/bar.ejs',{}) // uses ROOTFOLDER/views/bar.ejs\n</code></pre>", "src": "tutorials/rootfolder.md", "children": []})